.TH "memblock_isolate_range" 9 "memblock_isolate_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
memblock_isolate_range \- isolate given range into disjoint memblocks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int __init_memblock" memblock_isolate_range
.BI "(struct memblock_type *type "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t base "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t size "  ","
.BI "int *start_rgn "  ","
.BI "int *end_rgn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "type" 12
memblock type to isolate range for
.IP "base" 12
base of range to isolate
.IP "size" 12
size of range to isolate
.IP "start_rgn" 12
out parameter for the start of isolated region
.IP "end_rgn" 12
out parameter for the end of isolated region
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Walk \fItype\fP and ensure that regions don't cross the boundaries defined by
[\fIbase\fP, \fIbase\fP + \fIsize\fP).  Crossing regions are split at the boundaries,
which may create at most two more regions.  The index of the first
region inside the range is returned in *\fIstart_rgn\fP and end in *\fIend_rgn\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure.
